textBeforeTable: 2015 Tour Dates Low price $36 High price $131 Average Price $54 Past 12 Months Find Tickets Paul Kalkbrenner Ticket Prices Though Kalkbrenner's run with Bpitch ended in 2009, he has since established his own label and released the album "Icke Wieder," which contained no singing. His latest project, "Guten Tag," was released on November 30, 2012. Another project Kalkbrenner got involved in was the soundtrack to a film about a Berlin techno musician in 2006. Not only did he compose the entire thing, eventually he became the star of the screenplay that would be titled "Berlin Calling." And the film, while a smash in its own right, paled in comparison to the success of the single "Sky and Sand," which broke all sales records and stayed on the single charts for 121 weeks. Kalkbrenner may have gotten his start by buying all his own equipment to produce his own music, but it wasn't long before the ball started rolling downhill.
